  "original_title": "\u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0ba4\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd ; \u0b87\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bcb\u0b9f\u0bbf \u0bb5\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Presidential election; Indian Prime Minister Modi voted",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "Voting is taking place across the country from 10 am today to elect the new President in India.",
        "Prime Minister Modi and other leaders cast their ballots for the presidential election at the Parliament complex in Delhi.",
        "Voting for the election to elect the new president will take place today, Monday.",
        "Accordingly, Draupadi Murmu is the candidate of the National Democratic Alliance (BJP) and Yashwant Sinha is the candidate of the opposition party.",
        "MPs and MLAs across the country are going to vote for the new president.",
        "Polling has been arranged at the Chief Secretariat in the respective states for the MLAs to cast their votes.",
        "543 Lok Sabha MPs and 233 Rajya Sabha MPs from across the country were scheduled to vote in Parliament in Delhi.",
        "In this case, Prime Minister Modi cast ballots for the presidential election in the Delhi Parliament complex."
      ],
